      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 16:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " : and the suggestion in the marg. implies the adoption of a mode of marking time unknown either to himself or any other Scriptural writer. It is supposed that the figures here and in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 16:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " are corrupt, and that in both verses \"twentieth\" should replace \"thirtieth.\" The attack of Baasha would then have been made in the last year of Asa's reign; and ten years of peace would have followed Asa's victory over Zerah. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
